26:30.924 --> 26:35.137
She up and disappeared on me again.
She's got a way of doing that.

26:38.557 --> 26:43.020
- What do you think of Jessica?
- She's... She's very beautiful.

26:43.103 --> 26:46.732
Yeah, the main thing
about her, she's just...

26:46.773 --> 26:49.276
so full of life.

26:49.318 --> 26:52.112
We're a little different
in that respect.

26:52.196 --> 26:55.073
Oh.
I'm used to tennis shoes.

27:01.371 --> 27:03.373
This kind of reminds me
when I was a kid.

27:03.457 --> 27:06.668
I'd sit out on that porch.

27:06.752 --> 27:09.922
I'd have so many thoughts,
just couldn't count 'em.

27:10.005 --> 27:12.090
How'd you
wind up in Brixton?

27:12.132 --> 27:15.093
My husband. He got a job here
at the cable plant.

27:16.303 --> 27:18.263
Right.

27:20.974 --> 27:22.935
What?

27:25.145 --> 27:28.273
Did... Did you know...

27:28.315 --> 27:31.527
something was going
to happen to your husband?

27:35.113 --> 27:37.533
In an E.S.P. kind of way?

27:40.327 --> 27:44.206
- Well, I don't know...
- You don't believe in it.

27:46.959 --> 27:49.086
I don't know.
I guess I just...

27:51.338 --> 27:53.465
I don't believe there
are any great mysteries in life.

27:53.507 --> 27:56.552
I kind of figure what
you see is what you get.

28:01.974 --> 28:04.434
Well,

28:04.518 --> 28:07.312
I didn't know that there
was going to be an explosion.

28:07.396 --> 28:11.316
But... the night before,
I had this real bad,

28:11.358 --> 28:13.485
bad dream, you know.

28:13.527 --> 28:16.405
I dreamt that I was all by myself.
That Ben...

28:16.488 --> 28:20.117
He wasn't
around anymore and...

28:20.200 --> 28:23.328
tried to stop him going to work
the next day, but...

28:27.583 --> 28:29.960
So you can't keep
a good man from work, right?

28:36.758 --> 28:39.344
You kind
of remind me of him.

28:42.097 --> 28:44.683
Wayne?

28:44.725 --> 28:48.187
- I've been looking for you.
- I've been right here.

28:50.564 --> 28:52.691
I see.

28:55.027 --> 28:57.154
- Hi.
- Hi.

28:57.237 --> 29:00.073
Let's go talk to Daddy.
He's feeling real depressed tonight.

29:00.157 --> 29:02.034
That big deal
he's working on went bad.

29:02.075 --> 29:05.078
Oh, we got a major crisis
here, Annie. Excuse us?

29:06.205 --> 29:08.332
- Okay.
- Bye.

29:10.334 --> 29:12.461
See you later, alligator.

29:12.586 --> 29:15.088
- In a while, crocodile.
- Good night, boys.

29:15.172 --> 29:17.216
Go to sleep for Mama.

29:18.383 --> 29:20.969
- What's that, hon?
- Blueberry muffins.

29:21.053 --> 29:23.430
Whatcha doin' with muffins
in your pockets?

29:23.514 --> 29:25.557
Miss Francis cooked them.

29:25.641 --> 29:27.893
Yeah, but what are they
doing in your pockets?

29:27.976 --> 29:31.980
They're in my pockets 'cause I put
'em there when she wasn't looking...

29:32.064 --> 29:34.233
so I didn't
have to eat them.

29:34.274 --> 29:38.320
Her blueberry muffins is terrible.

29:41.073 --> 29:43.992
Y'all wait here a minute.
Take Ben, hon.

31:12.956 --> 31:16.919
When God's fighting for you,
every soldier's important.

31:16.960 --> 31:19.963
When God's fighting for you,
every soldier's important.

31:20.047 --> 31:22.341
God does not give
one to the Devil.

31:22.424 --> 31:24.801
If every child of God
obeyed God,

31:24.885 --> 31:26.803
the Devil cannot
wipe you out.

31:26.887 --> 31:29.097
He cannot take you out
before your time.

31:29.139 --> 31:31.099
If you obey God,
I don't care what the Devil...

31:31.141 --> 31:35.771
has placed upon your life,
Jesus can deliver you.

31:35.854 --> 31:39.441
Jesus came to bring you
out of your prison house.

31:39.525 --> 31:43.445
- Mama, is everything okay?
- Yeah, everything's fine.

31:43.487 --> 31:47.199
- You sure?
- Yeah. Time for you to go to bed.

31:49.952 --> 31:53.247
I know him. He's
a squirrel-hunting buddy of mine.

31:53.330 --> 31:56.917
- But I don't think that Donnie...
- I'm telling you it was him.

31:57.000 --> 32:00.128
What makes you think he'd want
to bust into your house?

32:00.212 --> 32:03.257
Well, his wife,
she's a client of mine,

32:03.340 --> 32:06.468
and he thinks I'm trying
to break up their marriage.

32:06.510 --> 32:08.929
Are you?

32:09.012 --> 32:12.599
Listen,
Donnie's high-strung.

32:12.683 --> 32:15.352
You know,
ain't no doubt about that.

32:15.435 --> 32:18.021
But I don't think he's the one
that busted into your house.

32:18.105 --> 32:21.441
Listen, I appreciate the coffee
and everything. Take care.

32:29.658 --> 32:33.412
I just can't get through
a wall of some kind in my head...

32:33.495 --> 32:36.665
or... or my soul.

32:36.707 --> 32:39.168
Sometimes I don't
even know the difference...

32:39.209 --> 32:42.379
between my head or my soul.

32:42.462 --> 32:45.174
I think everybody
has that trouble, Buddy.

32:48.844 --> 32:51.054
All right.

32:56.185 --> 32:58.478
Your daddy...

32:58.562 --> 33:02.357
He took things
away from you when you...

33:02.441 --> 33:04.902
when you were a little boy.

33:07.070 --> 33:09.865
Do you understand that?

33:11.700 --> 33:17.039
He... He seen me playing around with
something, like a toy or something,

33:17.122 --> 33:20.167
he'd just
take it away from me.

33:20.250 --> 33:22.878
Did he take other things
away from you?

33:29.134 --> 33:31.678
Buddy...

33:31.762 --> 33:33.889
You got to find out, hon,

33:33.931 --> 33:37.226
why you hate him so much.

33:37.267 --> 33:40.562
My daddy's a good man.
I don't hate my dad.

33:41.813 --> 33:44.024
He's good to Mama and me.

33:46.777 --> 33:50.614
Every kid needs a hit with a belt
sometime. I mean...

33:50.697 --> 33:55.202
Buddy, you got to try to get past
this wall that you're talking about.

33:56.495 --> 33:58.455
Hon, you need to talk
about your daddy.

33:58.539 --> 34:01.917
Why don't you tell me why I hate
him? You're the goddamn psychic!

34:01.959 --> 34:05.420
Huh?
You're the goddamn psychic!

34:24.022 --> 34:26.775
I think I better go.

34:26.859 --> 34:29.152
I have to go home,

34:32.822 --> 34:34.783
right now.

34:34.867 --> 34:37.661
I'm sorry
I yelled at you.

34:37.744 --> 34:39.788
It's all right.

34:41.123 --> 34:43.792
I just need...
I just need your help.

34:46.837 --> 34:50.132
I just keep thinking about that blue
diamond. I keep thinking about...

34:50.215 --> 34:55.137
Buddy, if you think about these
things in your childhood, hon,

34:55.179 --> 34:59.266
and you face up to them,
then I will be able to help you.

35:01.560 --> 35:03.812
I know, hon.
I just...

35:03.854 --> 35:07.274
I think you got to do
some thinking on your own.

35:09.735 --> 35:11.695
Okay.

35:11.737 --> 35:14.781
Oh. You...

35:14.865 --> 35:16.783
I'll help you there.

35:16.867 --> 35:20.245
- Okay, you put it up there.
- Hey, Ben.

35:20.329 --> 35:23.123
- Hello?
- You got a lot of pretty things.

35:23.207 --> 35:25.667
I liked looking at them.

35:25.709 --> 35:28.128
You ever seen anybody
skin a squirrel?

35:28.212 --> 35:30.964
You stick a knife
in its belly and zip.

35:31.048 --> 35:33.300
That's what I'm going to do
to you and your children...

35:33.383 --> 35:35.469
you ever call
the police again.

35:35.552 --> 35:37.513
I did not.

35:50.859 --> 35:52.903
Mama?

35:54.738 --> 35:56.949
Hey.

35:57.032 --> 36:00.828
- How come you're not asleep?
- I don't know.

36:03.580 --> 36:05.874
- What's that bat for?
- Oh.

36:05.916 --> 36:09.878
Don't worry, honey.
I'm... I'm just working on my swing.

36:11.713 --> 36:16.051
How come we never go
to the cemetery and see Daddy?

36:16.093 --> 36:20.097
Well, we went out there
just last month on his birthday.

36:21.348 --> 36:23.892
Honey, I'm real busy,
you know that.

36:23.934 --> 36:26.728
Well, it seems like you have time
for a lot of strangers.

36:26.812 --> 36:30.190
If we're talking about my
appointments, they're not strangers.

36:30.274 --> 36:32.651
They're the ones
that put food on our table.

36:32.734 --> 36:35.195
But how come we don't
even talk about Daddy?

36:35.279 --> 36:37.614
Go on, Mike.
I'm trying to read.

37:45.557 --> 37:47.684
- Annie?
- We're going to have to frame that.

37:47.768 --> 37:49.728
- It's just a painting.
- That's beautiful.

37:49.811 --> 37:52.648
- Annie.
- Hey.

37:52.731 --> 37:56.235
Hey, listen. I know why Kenneth King
wasn't in church today.

37:56.318 --> 38:00.280
- Put your belt on. Why?
- 'Cause his daughter disappeared.

38:00.364 --> 38:02.241
Jessica?

38:02.324 --> 38:04.243
What do you mean
she disappeared?

38:04.326 --> 38:06.912
Well, Kenneth woke up this morning
and Jessica wasn't there,

38:06.995 --> 38:08.664
and her bed
hadn't even been slept in.

38:08.747 --> 38:11.083
Annie, you think
she ran off?

38:11.166 --> 38:13.585
I know her and Wayne were
supposed to be married in June.

38:13.669 --> 38:16.588
- Maybe she got cold feet.
- Maybe.

38:16.672 --> 38:19.466
Maybe this will clear
the way for you and Wayne.

38:20.676 --> 38:23.178
- What are you talking about?
- Oh, come on.

38:23.262 --> 38:26.807
I saw the way y'all were looking
at each other Friday night.

38:26.890 --> 38:29.351
Y'all both just
had stars in your eyes.

38:29.393 --> 38:31.854
Oh, Linda, that's nuts.

38:31.895 --> 38:35.691
- Yeah. Annie, love is nuts.
- Come on. Go home.

38:35.732 --> 38:39.194
Listen,
I want you to get some rest.

38:39.278 --> 38:41.822
You look terrible, okay?
Bye, boys.

38:41.905 --> 38:44.366
- I got to go.
- Bye, Miss Linda.

38:59.047 --> 39:01.383
Ben, get your hand
out of there!

39:01.425 --> 39:03.385
That's for y'all's
cake tonight.

39:03.427 --> 39:06.847
- What am I gonna ice the cake with?
- I like icin', Mama.

39:06.889 --> 39:09.308
Yeah,
I can see that, punkin.

39:09.391 --> 39:11.351
Miller!

39:12.811 --> 39:14.730
Miller, hon, would you
go ask Miss Francis...

39:14.813 --> 39:17.399
if she's got another
can of icing, please?

39:17.482 --> 39:20.110
- Mama!
- I'm coming, Ben.

39:41.590 --> 39:44.343
Where you going, son?

39:48.972 --> 39:51.225
You wanna ride
in the truck?

39:54.311 --> 39:58.440
I got a question for you.
You know my wife Valerie?

39:58.524 --> 40:01.068
She been around
to see your mama lately?

40:02.361 --> 40:05.572
Hey, boy,
I asked you a question.

40:07.366 --> 40:09.409
Get my hat.

40:16.208 --> 40:19.044
You know, I feel sorry
for you and your brothers.

40:19.127 --> 40:22.089
I mean, your mama
being a witch and all.

40:22.130 --> 40:24.466
If she don't stop
her evil ways,

40:24.550 --> 40:27.010
some day somebody's
gonna burn her up.

40:27.094 --> 40:30.055
And then you boys
are gonna be without a daddy...

40:30.138 --> 40:32.599
or a mama.

40:32.683 --> 40:36.562
Hey, Miller?
You all right?

40:36.645 --> 40:39.940
He said mama's a witch
and they're gonna burn her up.

40:39.982 --> 40:41.984
Oh, he did?

40:46.905 --> 40:50.367
- You better mind your own business.
- I intend to, Donnie.

40:58.584 --> 41:00.586
Motherfucker!

41:00.669 --> 41:03.130
Goddamn it! Fuck!

41:03.172 --> 41:05.174
Look, fucker!

41:06.884 --> 41:08.844
Shoot me!
Shoot me!

41:08.886 --> 41:11.471
Shoot me,
you motherfucker!

41:11.555 --> 41:14.516
Shoot me! Shoot me!

41:31.533 --> 41:33.827
You all right?

41:45.839 --> 41:48.675
Tuscan Rouge.

41:48.759 --> 41:50.886
What was I thinking?

41:53.555 --> 41:55.849
I want icin', Mama.

41:55.891 --> 41:58.018
Hon, you've had icing enough
to put you in a coma.

41:58.060 --> 42:00.062
And from now on,

42:00.103 --> 42:02.064
I want to know where you all are
every minute of the day.

42:02.147 --> 42:04.274
All right?

42:05.692 --> 42:08.278
Mike, I'm gonna start
driving you and Miller to school.

42:09.988 --> 42:12.699
I wish Daddy was here.

42:12.741 --> 42:17.496
Well, he's not, hon.
But Mama is. Okay?

42:23.794 --> 42:25.712
Eat your cake.

42:28.757 --> 42:31.426
- Hello.
- This is Kenneth King.

42:31.510 --> 42:35.055
- Mr. King.
- I imagine you,

42:35.264 --> 42:38.100
heard about
my daughter's disappearance?

42:38.141 --> 42:39.852
- Yes.
- Well...

42:39.935 --> 42:41.895
Mrs. Wilson,
I don't believe in what you do.

42:41.979 --> 42:43.939
I'll just be
straight with you.

42:44.022 --> 42:48.569
Not only that, I don't like it. But
we've got to the end of the road...

42:48.610 --> 42:52.239
and our investigation looked under
every rock there is to look under,

42:52.281 --> 42:55.742
and we'd like you to tell us
what you can to help us.

42:55.784 --> 42:59.246
Now, no hocus-pocus
and chanting and carrying on.

42:59.329 --> 43:03.208
We know you talk to a lot of folks,
know a lot of folks' business.

43:03.292 --> 43:07.254
You might have heard
something or something.

43:07.337 --> 43:09.131
The only thing we know is,

43:09.214 --> 43:13.093
one of Sheriff Johnson's men
found my daughter's car...

43:13.135 --> 43:16.263
sitting out on the parking lot
of that honky-tonk called AyJay's.

43:16.346 --> 43:19.308
But nobody that was there
on Saturday night...

43:19.349 --> 43:21.643
admits to having seen her.

43:21.727 --> 43:25.981
So I'm afraid she might have been
kidnapped or something?

43:27.649 --> 43:30.819
Oh, Mr. King,
I'm... I'm sorry.

43:30.903 --> 43:33.822
I don't know anything about
your daughter's disappearance.

43:33.864 --> 43:36.366
I think
we were just hoping...

43:37.534 --> 43:39.995
Is there anything
you can tell us?

43:40.078 --> 43:42.456
I could read for you.

43:43.874 --> 43:47.336
But that... that's
about all I could do.

43:47.419 --> 43:50.047
I need you
to cut the cards for me.

44:00.307 --> 44:02.226
Oh, boy.

44:08.065 --> 44:10.067
Thank you.

44:17.032 --> 44:19.535
All right.
You ready?

44:21.078 --> 44:23.247
Okay.

44:31.046 --> 44:33.674
When were you
getting married again, Wayne?

44:33.715 --> 44:36.343
- June 20...
- We're supposed to ask questions,

44:36.385 --> 44:38.345
- not you.
- Shut up, Pearl! Goddamn it!

44:38.387 --> 44:40.347
Look, I have a hard time
concentrating...

44:40.389 --> 44:43.016
with more than one person
in the room.

44:43.058 --> 44:47.062
Well, I'm staying right here. I'm
the law, and I need to hear this.

44:47.145 --> 44:50.232
Please, ma'am, just...

44:50.315 --> 44:51.650
just try to tell us
what you see.

44:51.650 --> 44:52.901
just try to tell us
what you see.

44:52.943 --> 44:55.737
I'm trying.

44:55.779 --> 44:57.948
All right.

45:16.383 --> 45:18.343
All right,
all I'm picking up...

45:18.427 --> 45:22.556
it's like a...
it's a fence.

45:22.598 --> 45:25.893
Like a split rail fence.

45:25.934 --> 45:28.770
Do you know how many fences
there are in this county?

45:30.272 --> 45:33.233
And some pillars, like,
with an opening going through.

45:38.280 --> 45:42.117
And there's lots of white flowers.
I can... I...

45:42.159 --> 45:46.830
Yes. And,
is that where Jessie is?

45:58.383 --> 46:02.930
Well, that's... that's, all I'm...
all I'm seeing.

46:03.013 --> 46:06.391
This is just mishmash. I told you
this wouldn't lead to nothing.

46:06.475 --> 46:09.436
You're right. It won't.
I can't concentrate.

46:11.146 --> 46:15.234
- I can't do this now. I'm sorry.
- Please, ma'am.

46:15.317 --> 46:17.319
I really do hope
you find your daughter.

46:17.402 --> 46:21.490
But I'm... I'm just not the person
to help you with this.

49:03.777 --> 49:05.779
Hey, Butch.

49:39.104 --> 49:41.023
And it was horrible.

49:41.106 --> 49:44.026
But that same chain that was wrapped
around her when she was floatin',

49:44.109 --> 49:49.198
you know, up in my tree, it was the
same chain that I had in my dream.

49:49.281 --> 49:52.284
- I don't know. I just thought...
- Dave?

49:54.786 --> 49:57.164
Yes, sir?

49:57.206 --> 49:59.208
I could have sworn there
was an eclair in there.

49:59.249 --> 50:02.419
I didn't get it.

50:04.505 --> 50:07.216
Tim was in
a little earlier.

50:10.552 --> 50:12.346
So you saw all this
in a dream?

50:12.387 --> 50:14.348
It wasn't just a dream.

50:14.389 --> 50:16.475
I don't investigate
somebody's dream.

50:18.018 --> 50:20.062
I think she's dead, Sheriff.

50:20.145 --> 50:23.190
And I think she's in a pond.

50:23.232 --> 50:26.735
What do you know about this
you ain't telling me?

50:26.819 --> 50:30.030
You can get in serious
trouble with holding information.

50:30.072 --> 50:32.157
Does it sound like
a place you know?

50:32.241 --> 50:34.201
Yeah,
a bunch of places I know.

50:34.243 --> 50:37.496
Split rail fence, a pond,
a stretch of woods.

50:37.579 --> 50:40.207
- Every raw bone ol' boy got that.
- What about the fiddler?

50:40.249 --> 50:43.293
Well,

50:43.377 --> 50:45.754
ol' Tommy Lee Ballard
plays a fiddle.

50:45.838 --> 50:48.465
But he wouldn't kill nobody.
I've known him since he's a kid.

50:48.549 --> 50:52.052
No, no, it's not the fiddler.
Who are his neighbors?

50:52.094 --> 50:56.014
Well, his closest neighbor
would be...

50:57.266 --> 51:00.102
Well, let me see here.
I guess...

51:00.143 --> 51:04.398
Well, his property borders,
Donnie Barksdale's place.

51:05.774 --> 51:08.110
Do you know
Donnie Barksdale?

51:10.237 --> 51:12.239
Ma'am?

51:19.121 --> 51:21.373
Tim! On the gate!

51:22.749 --> 51:24.668
You did get
a search warrant, didn't you?

51:24.751 --> 51:26.670
I want everything
to be legal and proper.

51:26.753 --> 51:29.131
Didn't have to.
Got permission from the owner.

51:29.173 --> 51:32.467
Donnie Barksdale
gave you permission...

51:32.509 --> 51:36.096
His wife did.
I told her it was routine.

51:36.138 --> 51:38.473
We're checking all the ponds
in the county.

51:38.515 --> 51:40.684
Donnie's gone fishing today.

51:57.201 --> 51:59.745
Excuse me. Sheriff Johnson?

51:59.828 --> 52:03.665
- How much longer y'all gonna be?
- Long as it takes.

52:03.707 --> 52:07.127
All right. You just said you're
gonna be a few minutes.

52:07.169 --> 52:09.546
And we're
going on two hours.

52:09.630 --> 52:12.633
Hey, Pearl!
I think I got something!

52:41.870 --> 52:45.082
False alarm.
It's just an old bicycle.

52:48.585 --> 52:51.255
None of y'all brought a Thermos
of coffee out here?

53:14.778 --> 53:16.864
That day at school.

53:18.198 --> 53:21.118
You looked kind of strange
at me and Jessica.

53:21.201 --> 53:23.662
Did you think
something bad then?

53:34.298 --> 53:36.758
Shit.
Come on.

53:38.051 --> 53:41.054
- Donnie, he called. I told him...
- Pearl!

53:41.096 --> 53:43.182
Shut your mouth!

53:43.265 --> 53:45.350
Goddamn it, Pearl,
what are you doing on my property?

53:45.434 --> 53:48.854
I'm on Sheriff's business, Donnie.
I got permission from your wife.

53:48.937 --> 53:50.856
You think I let that
little ninny talk for me?

53:52.774 --> 53:55.444
How'd your arm
get all scratched up?

53:57.696 --> 54:01.241
Stray cat. She didn't like it
when I killed her.

54:01.283 --> 54:04.661
- Now what brought you here?
- Just routine investigation.

54:04.745 --> 54:06.955
We're checking
all the ponds in the county.

54:14.588 --> 54:18.008
- I knew it was you.
- No! You!

54:21.803 --> 54:25.349
Hey! I'm on County business,
Donnie. Don't fool with me.

54:25.432 --> 54:28.185
- Hey, Pearl!
- What?

54:28.268 --> 54:31.188
- You need to take a look at this.
- Watch him.

54:31.271 --> 54:34.274
Hault up, boys!

54:42.324 --> 54:45.410
- It's her!
- Donnie?

54:48.288 --> 54:51.667
Get those hooks
out of my baby!

54:51.708 --> 54:54.878
- Get her off them hooks!
- Cuff him!

54:54.962 --> 54:58.257
- No! No!
- Mr. King!

55:00.676 --> 55:03.804
- No!
- Get an ambulance!

55:03.846 --> 55:05.806
I think he's
having a heart attack!

55:05.848 --> 55:08.433
- I didn't do this!
- Get him out of here!

55:08.517 --> 55:10.686
This ain't right!
Pearl!

55:10.727 --> 55:15.023
Bitch! Bitch!
Bitch! Pearl!

55:29.121 --> 55:31.415
Come in.

55:34.334 --> 55:36.253
Somebody might
come in here.

55:36.336 --> 55:39.047
I guess you better
fuck me fast.

55:39.089 --> 55:42.009
You want some coffee?
Mrs. Wilson?

55:44.761 --> 55:47.014
You want some coffee?

55:47.055 --> 55:49.349
No, thank you.

55:49.391 --> 55:51.351
Have a seat.

55:56.857 --> 55:59.151
Why... Why have you
called me here?

55:59.234 --> 56:02.446
Tomorrow Donnie Barksdale goes
on trial for murder...

56:02.529 --> 56:05.616
and I feel
that we have a powerful case.

56:05.699 --> 56:07.618
In fact,
today the coroner verified...

56:07.701 --> 56:10.037
Donnie's tissue
under the victim's fingernails.

56:10.078 --> 56:13.749
Now, I only have one weak link
I got to worry about.

56:13.832 --> 56:17.044
- What?
- You.

56:17.085 --> 56:21.423
You see, you're how we found out
where the victim's body was.

56:21.465 --> 56:24.760
And how you found out,
well,

56:24.843 --> 56:28.055
that might open up
a real can of worms for us.

56:28.096 --> 56:32.643
Psychic phenomena,
E.S.P., dreams, visions.

56:32.726 --> 56:34.978
The defense
could go to town on you.

56:35.062 --> 56:38.273
And if that's not bad enough,
I understand there was bad blood...

56:38.357 --> 56:41.276
between you
and Donnie Barksdale.

56:41.318 --> 56:43.570
Yeah.
He threatened my kids.

56:43.612 --> 56:47.574
That's what I heard. I also heard
that you threatened him right back.

56:47.658 --> 56:49.785
Told his wife
to leave him.

56:52.204 --> 56:54.665
Donnie's quite
a ladies' man.

56:54.748 --> 56:56.959
Were you involved
with him?

56:59.044 --> 57:01.296
- What?
- I can deal with any revelation...

57:01.380 --> 57:03.298
right now.

57:03.382 --> 57:06.301
But at the trial
there can't be any surprises.

57:07.970 --> 57:10.639
So, is there anything I need
to know about you or Donnie...

57:10.722 --> 57:13.976
or Donnie's wife
or the victim?

57:14.017 --> 57:16.478
No.

57:16.562 --> 57:18.856
Will that be all?

57:20.023 --> 57:21.984
Yes, ma'am.

57:24.778 --> 57:28.198
You know, Mr. Duncan,

57:28.282 --> 57:31.743
the victim had a name.

57:31.827 --> 57:34.496
It was Jessica King.

57:38.333 --> 57:39.918
Mr. Hawkins, how long have you
worked out at AyJay's?

57:39.918 --> 57:42.087
Mr. Hawkins, how long have you
worked out at AyJay's?

57:42.171 --> 57:44.089
About ten years.

57:44.173 --> 57:47.718
Now, were you working at AyJay's
on Saturday night, April 8?

57:47.801 --> 57:50.345
- Yes, sir.
- And did you see the defendant,

57:50.429 --> 57:54.183
- Donnie Barksdale, there that night?
- Yes, sir.

57:54.266 --> 57:57.019
Could you describe the circumstances
when you saw him?

57:57.060 --> 58:01.857
The circumstances were I come
outside to throw out some trash.

58:01.899 --> 58:03.859
And do you recall
what time it was?

58:03.901 --> 58:06.195
About midnight,
I reckon.

58:06.278 --> 58:09.823
Anyhow, I seen Donnie Barksdale
out there by his truck...

58:09.907 --> 58:13.827
havin' an argument
with this white lady.

58:13.869 --> 58:18.665
She scratched his arm
and he slapped the tar out of her.

58:18.707 --> 58:21.543
About that time,
I go back inside.

58:21.627 --> 58:23.962
Is this the woman
you saw with Donnie Barksdale?

58:24.046 --> 58:27.257
- Yes, sir.
- Your Honor, let the record show...

58:27.341 --> 58:31.345
that I've just shown Mr. Hawkins
a photograph of Jessica King.

58:33.847 --> 58:39.019
You just said that your attention
was drawn to the defendant's pond.

58:40.354 --> 58:43.357
Drawn in...
Well, drawn in what way?

58:44.733 --> 58:47.569
Me, Wayne Collins
and Kenneth King...

58:47.611 --> 58:49.571
went to see a woman,
name of Annie Wilson.

58:49.613 --> 58:52.074
What made you think this woman
would be able to help you?

58:52.115 --> 58:57.913
Well, word around town
was that she was a...

59:00.833 --> 59:04.878
- Well, I don't know the right word.
- Isn't it fortune-teller?

59:06.672 --> 59:08.924
- I guess so.
- What did this fortune-teller see...

59:09.007 --> 59:11.969
when she looked into
her little crystal ball?

59:12.010 --> 59:16.849
Well, she didn't have no ball.
She had these, special cards.

59:16.932 --> 59:20.185
What did she see when she looked
into her little special cards?

59:20.269 --> 59:22.521
She didn't actually
see nothing then.

59:22.604 --> 59:26.108
But next day,
she come to see me and...

59:26.191 --> 59:28.068
told me
she had this dream.

59:28.152 --> 59:31.155
- She had a dream?
- Yes, sir.

59:31.238 --> 59:35.450
She'd seen this pond and it looked
a lot like Donnie Barksdale's and...

59:37.035 --> 59:39.621
then she woke up
from her dream...

59:39.705 --> 59:42.749
and she went outside
and looked up in this tree.

59:45.794 --> 59:47.796
I'm all ears.

59:51.800 --> 59:54.887
She seen Jessica King...

59:54.970 --> 59:57.598
floatin' in the tree,

59:57.681 --> 01:00:00.476
half-naked, with a chain
wrapped around her.

01:00:00.517 --> 01:00:02.936
Floatin' around a tree?

01:00:04.396 --> 01:00:06.356
Yes, sir.

01:00:07.858 --> 01:00:09.818
Floatin' in a tree,

01:00:09.902 --> 01:00:11.987
half-naked,

01:00:13.906 --> 01:00:16.200
with a chain
wrapped around her.

01:00:16.241 --> 01:00:18.577
Thank you, Sheriff.

01:00:20.078 --> 01:00:22.581
That little squirrel,
Weems, is just mean and skinny.

01:00:22.664 --> 01:00:25.167
Never have known
a Weems worth a damn.

01:00:25.250 --> 01:00:27.127
Well, he was
just doing his job.

01:00:27.211 --> 01:00:31.048
Mrs. Wilson?
Can I talk to you for a minute?

01:00:31.089 --> 01:00:34.426
Just call me later on, okay?

01:00:34.510 --> 01:00:36.428
- Oh, okay.
- Okay, bye.

01:00:36.512 --> 01:00:41.141
Buddy, I got a lot on my mind.
It's not a good time, okay?

01:00:43.477 --> 01:00:45.395
Mrs. Wilson?

01:00:45.479 --> 01:00:49.525
You did tell me to do some thinkin'
and talkin'. And I've been thinkin'.

01:00:49.608 --> 01:00:51.401
What? What?

01:00:51.443 --> 01:00:55.322
Can you tell me why
I do things to myself...

01:00:55.405 --> 01:00:57.324
when I think
about my daddy?

01:00:57.407 --> 01:00:59.493
All right, well...

01:00:59.576 --> 01:01:03.789
Bud, you call me later, hon,
and we'll talk, all right?

01:01:03.872 --> 01:01:06.667
- I need to talk to you.
- Buddy.

01:01:06.750 --> 01:01:09.670
I've been thinking about my daddy
and I've been touching myself.

01:01:09.753 --> 01:01:12.673
- Touching yourself? How?
- Why do I do that?

01:01:12.756 --> 01:01:14.299
It's not a good time.

01:01:14.383 --> 01:01:17.636
- Something's bad wrong with me.
- Look, Buddy...

01:01:17.719 --> 01:01:20.681
And I... I keep thinking
about that blue diamond.

01:01:20.764 --> 01:01:24.560
You look into the blue diamond,
you won't think a negative thought.

01:01:24.643 --> 01:01:28.438
I promise. Now, hon, I'm going
through a hard time myself. I'm...

01:01:28.480 --> 01:01:31.775
I just... I can't talk
to you now, okay?

01:01:35.112 --> 01:01:37.739
You're gonna burn
in hell, Annie Wilson!

01:01:48.417 --> 01:01:51.587
Now, Mike, I know you skipped
school and went to that trial.

01:01:51.670 --> 01:01:54.756
- How'd you know?
- A little bird told me.

01:01:54.840 --> 01:01:58.051
It's time you started making things
easier on me instead of harder.

01:01:58.135 --> 01:02:00.053
I'm very disappointed in you.

01:02:00.137 --> 01:02:03.599
- The phone's ringing, Mama.
- Second of all,

01:02:03.682 --> 01:02:06.477
I'm gonna have to testify
at that trial tomorrow.

01:02:06.518 --> 01:02:09.354
- The phone's ringing, Mama.
- I'm not deaf, Miller.

01:02:09.438 --> 01:02:11.607
Let the machine get it.

01:02:11.690 --> 01:02:15.611
Donnie Barksdale's side, they're
gonna try and give me a hard time.

01:02:15.694 --> 01:02:18.280
They're gonna call me names
and I...

01:02:18.322 --> 01:02:20.282
I just want y'all
to be prepared...

01:02:20.324 --> 01:02:23.619
if you hear any bad stuff
about me, all right?

01:02:23.660 --> 01:02:27.164
Now, we're all gonna have to
be sticking together on this one.

01:02:27.247 --> 01:02:30.000
Annie Wilson, it's Buddy's mother.

01:02:30.042 --> 01:02:32.628
Buddy's done gone crazy.
He's threatening to kill his daddy!

01:02:32.711 --> 01:02:36.548
He's got Odell tied up
in the backyard,

01:02:36.632 --> 01:02:38.634
accusing him
of horrible things.

01:02:38.717 --> 01:02:42.179
- Have you called the police?
- He said if I did he'd kill Odell.

01:02:42.221 --> 01:02:44.515
He wants you.

01:02:46.558 --> 01:02:49.269
Hey, Buddy.

01:02:50.979 --> 01:02:55.984
Buddy, put that strap down and
tell me what he's done to you.

01:02:56.026 --> 01:02:59.279
I'm here, Buddy. Like you said,
you can talk to me, honey.

01:02:59.363 --> 01:03:04.701
It's too late for that!
It's too goddamn late!

01:03:04.743 --> 01:03:08.539
This here is a criminal.

01:03:10.624 --> 01:03:13.126
And he's gonna be punished.

01:03:13.210 --> 01:03:15.671
Bud-Buddy.
Buddy, it's Annie.

01:03:15.754 --> 01:03:18.841
- You shut up! You shut up!
- It's all right.

01:03:18.924 --> 01:03:22.970
- Get away! Where were you?
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

01:03:23.053 --> 01:03:27.474
You knew everything
and you did nothing.

01:03:27.558 --> 01:03:30.310
You ruined me.
You ruined me!

01:03:32.229 --> 01:03:34.064
I was just a little boy, Daddy.

01:03:34.106 --> 01:03:37.609
It got so I was embarrassed
to go to school, Daddy.

01:03:37.693 --> 01:03:40.445
How could you do that
to your little boy?

01:03:52.875 --> 01:03:55.502
No, Buddy. You put that down.
No, Buddy.

01:03:55.586 --> 01:03:58.547
You put that down, Buddy.
You put that down. You listen to me.

01:03:58.589 --> 01:04:01.842
You get away!
You get away! Get away!

01:04:01.925 --> 01:04:06.305
All right, Buddy. All right.
It's all right. Come on.

01:04:07.806 --> 01:04:10.100
Why... Why didn't
you help me, Annie?

01:04:10.142 --> 01:04:11.935
What?

01:04:11.977 --> 01:04:14.730
Why didn't you
help me?

01:04:14.771 --> 01:04:18.358
- I had you for a friend and then...
- I am your friend, Buddy.

01:04:18.442 --> 01:04:21.111
Now I have nobody.

01:04:21.153 --> 01:04:23.113
I have nobody!

01:04:34.625 --> 01:04:36.627
But I'm gonna...
I'm gonna kill this thing.

01:04:37.961 --> 01:04:40.088
- No!
- No, Buddy!

01:04:45.177 --> 01:04:46.595
No!

01:04:47.971 --> 01:04:49.431
Help me!

01:04:49.515 --> 01:04:52.684
- Help me!
- Look at that goddamn thing.

01:04:52.768 --> 01:04:54.978
And you tell me what kind
of thoughts you have?

01:04:55.020 --> 01:04:58.065
You look!

01:04:58.148 --> 01:05:00.067
You look
into that thing!

01:05:21.255 --> 01:05:24.675
Mrs. Wilson? Mrs. Wilson.

01:05:26.051 --> 01:05:29.221
Mrs. Wilson, your husband,
Ben Wilson Senior,

01:05:29.304 --> 01:05:31.765
was one of the men killed last year
in the explosion...

01:05:31.849 --> 01:05:33.767
out at the Reinhold
Cable Plant.

01:05:33.851 --> 01:05:35.936
Yes, that's right.

01:05:36.019 --> 01:05:39.439
And you were left with three small
children to raise on your own.

01:05:39.523 --> 01:05:41.984
Yes, sir.

01:05:42.067 --> 01:05:44.486
How do you provide
for you and your sons?

01:05:48.949 --> 01:05:51.827
I get a little bit
of money from Social Security...

01:05:51.869 --> 01:05:53.829
as a result
of my husband's death.

01:05:56.456 --> 01:05:58.959
And,

01:05:59.042 --> 01:06:01.295
I also give readings.

01:06:01.336 --> 01:06:03.380
- Psychic readings.
- Yes, sir.

01:06:03.463 --> 01:06:06.425
What does being psychic
enable you to do?

01:06:08.427 --> 01:06:10.637
I see things...

01:06:10.679 --> 01:06:14.141
and I, you know...
I sense... things...

01:06:14.183 --> 01:06:16.310
that... well, they
hadn't happened yet...

01:06:16.351 --> 01:06:19.563
or they were happening
someplace else.

01:06:19.646 --> 01:06:24.818
My granny told me that I...
I had a gift that runs in my family.

01:06:24.860 --> 01:06:27.154
And she told me that
I shouldn't be afraid of it.

01:06:27.237 --> 01:06:32.326
I should just always use my instinct
and I'd... I'd be all right.

01:06:32.409 --> 01:06:34.411
So, you're swearing
before this court...

01:06:34.495 --> 01:06:36.663
that you didn't get your information
about this tragedy...

01:06:36.705 --> 01:06:39.583
from any other means
than your special ability?

01:06:39.666 --> 01:06:42.628
- Your gift.
- Yes, sir.

01:06:42.711 --> 01:06:45.464
I'm swearing that. Yes.

01:06:45.547 --> 01:06:48.509
- Thank you, Mrs. Wilson.
- Yes, sir.

01:06:48.592 --> 01:06:51.303
- I have no further questions.
- Mr. Weems.

01:06:56.225 --> 01:06:57.684
Mrs. Wilson.

01:07:01.605 --> 01:07:04.149
How many fingers am I holding up
behind my back?

01:07:04.233 --> 01:07:06.193
- Objection, Your Honor.
- Your Honor,

01:07:06.235 --> 01:07:08.987
my client is sitting in this
courtroom on trial for his life...

01:07:09.071 --> 01:07:12.533
partly because of powers
that this woman claims to have.

01:07:12.616 --> 01:07:15.536
Now, in all fairness, I believe
I should be given the opportunity...

01:07:15.619 --> 01:07:17.538
to test
the alleged powers...

01:07:17.621 --> 01:07:20.165
instead of having to stand here
and take her word for it.

01:07:20.249 --> 01:07:23.669
You have a good point.
Objection overruled.

01:07:23.752 --> 01:07:29.132
Can everyone in the jury box
see how many fingers I'm showing?

01:07:33.595 --> 01:07:35.806
How many fingers,
Mrs. Wilson?

01:07:41.478 --> 01:07:43.397
I don't know.

01:07:43.480 --> 01:07:45.691
You don't know?

01:07:48.277 --> 01:07:51.697
Seven.
Seven fingers.

01:07:51.780 --> 01:07:54.408
That... That doesn't
prove anything.

01:07:54.491 --> 01:07:57.619
Your Honor, I can't do this,
you know, at the drop of a hat.

01:07:57.703 --> 01:08:02.082
Well, then, ma'am, how about doing
it at the drop of a dollar bill?

01:08:02.124 --> 01:08:04.418
What are you trying to say?

01:08:04.459 --> 01:08:06.879
I'm trying to say maybe this special
gift of yours doesn't work...

01:08:06.962 --> 01:08:09.673
unless you're
being paid for it.

01:08:09.756 --> 01:08:12.176
Like they say in the army,
''No money, no honey.''

01:08:12.259 --> 01:08:14.219
No, that's not true.

01:08:14.303 --> 01:08:16.220
Are you aware that in Hatcher County
it's against the law...

01:08:16.305 --> 01:08:18.432
for a psychic to set up shop
and charge people money?

01:08:18.515 --> 01:08:20.517
Well, I don't charge money.

01:08:20.600 --> 01:08:22.560
You just testified
that you do charge money.

01:08:22.644 --> 01:08:26.023
No. I accept donations.
People give me gifts.

01:08:26.106 --> 01:08:30.777
Oh. A distinction
worthy of a lawyer.

01:08:30.819 --> 01:08:33.322
Mrs. Wilson,
you a rich woman?

01:08:33.404 --> 01:08:35.407
- No.
- Why not?

01:08:35.491 --> 01:08:40.412
If I had psychic powers and could
read the future, I'd be filthy rich.

01:08:40.496 --> 01:08:42.413
I'd be playing
the Stock Market.

01:08:42.456 --> 01:08:45.459
I'd be over in Mobile
betting on the dogs.

01:08:45.501 --> 01:08:47.794
I'd certainly warn my husband
not to go to work...

01:08:47.836 --> 01:08:50.296
on the day I know the Reinhold
Plant's gonna blow up...

01:08:50.339 --> 01:08:54.593
leaving three little ol' children
to be raised in a carnival sideshow.

01:08:54.676 --> 01:08:57.970
Well, it doesn't work
that way, sir.

01:08:58.013 --> 01:08:59.973
I can't use my gift
for personal gain.

01:09:00.057 --> 01:09:05.312
Except for those,
what you call 'em, donations?

01:09:09.066 --> 01:09:13.569
You've had some personal trouble
with Donnie Barksdale, haven't you?

01:09:18.826 --> 01:09:20.743
Yes, I have.

01:09:20.828 --> 01:09:23.663
Just a few weeks ago, you told him...
I believe the exact words was...

01:09:23.705 --> 01:09:25.999
you was gonna have
his ass thrown in jail.

01:09:26.041 --> 01:09:28.836
- But he was threatening my kids.
- Ain't it also true...

01:09:28.877 --> 01:09:31.839
that a few weeks ago in one of
those famous readings of yours,

01:09:31.880 --> 01:09:33.841
when you were doing
your so-called E.S.P.,

01:09:33.881 --> 01:09:36.176
you told Valerie Barksdale,
Donnie's wife,

01:09:36.260 --> 01:09:38.636
that Donnie was just
an insecure redneck...

01:09:38.720 --> 01:09:41.640
and that he wasn't really
crazy enough to kill anybody?

01:09:48.397 --> 01:09:50.357
Yes, I did say that.

01:09:50.399 --> 01:09:52.651
Then why today are you
saying he did kill somebody?

01:09:52.693 --> 01:09:54.653
Wait a second.
I've never said that.

01:09:54.695 --> 01:09:57.239
You might as well have, ma'am.
You wanted his ass in jail.

01:09:57.322 --> 01:10:00.701
- He's on trial for his life.
- I just told the sheriff what I saw.

01:10:00.742 --> 01:10:04.329
And how could any of us
ever forget that?

01:10:05.747 --> 01:10:08.208
Jessica King just
floatin' up in that tree,

01:10:08.250 --> 01:10:10.794
naked,

01:10:10.878 --> 01:10:13.338
with a chain...

01:10:13.422 --> 01:10:15.382
wrapped around her.

01:10:17.134 --> 01:10:20.804
It must be
so much fun for you.

01:10:20.888 --> 01:10:23.056
You must be having
the time of your life...

01:10:23.098 --> 01:10:26.185
entertaining yourself
with your dreams and your visions.

01:10:26.268 --> 01:10:29.855
You think it's fun seeing decomposed
bodies in my tree, do you, sir?

01:10:29.938 --> 01:10:31.857
You think that's fun?

01:10:31.940 --> 01:10:35.319
Do you think it's fun I have people
trying to strangle me in my sleep?

01:10:35.402 --> 01:10:37.571
Now I'm sitting here
and I'm blaming myself...

01:10:37.613 --> 01:10:40.073
'cause some poor crazy man tried
to burn his daddy half to death.

01:10:40.115 --> 01:10:42.075
And you think I'm sitting here
having fun?

01:10:42.117 --> 01:10:44.912
I'm sorry, sir.
You're crazy if you think that.

01:10:44.995 --> 01:10:47.748
No more questions,
Your Honor.

01:10:49.291 --> 01:10:51.251
You're dismissed.

01:11:04.306 --> 01:11:06.892
Like they say in Hollywood,
let's just cut to the chase.

01:11:06.975 --> 01:11:10.187
Did you or did you not
kill Jessica King?

01:11:10.270 --> 01:11:12.189
I did not.

01:11:12.272 --> 01:11:15.901
Did you or did you not see Jessica
King on the night she was killed?

01:11:15.984 --> 01:11:19.238
Yeah, I seen her.

01:11:19.321 --> 01:11:21.782
Would you describe
the circumstances, please?

