You don't... I mean, do you know
what it was like with her?

01:38:23.904 --> 01:38:27.574
She was so fucking hurtful
and spiteful and all of it...

01:38:27.658 --> 01:38:29.243
Wayne, I'm not gonna...

01:38:29.326 --> 01:38:31.995
But all of it just happened
in this flash of a moment.

01:38:32.079 --> 01:38:35.541
- Wayne, I...
- Listen to me. I'm a good man.

01:38:35.624 --> 01:38:38.877
If it had been you instead of her,
none of this would have happened.

01:38:38.961 --> 01:38:41.130
Wayne.

01:38:44.007 --> 01:38:45.968
It's all right, you know?

01:38:46.009 --> 01:38:49.263
I won't... I won't tell.

01:38:52.349 --> 01:38:55.477
I won't...
I won't tell anybody.

01:38:57.187 --> 01:38:59.231
No, Annie...

01:40:12.888 --> 01:40:15.224
You all right, Mrs. Wilson?

01:41:04.106 --> 01:41:07.985
I thought you were supposed to
be in the hospital.

01:41:08.068 --> 01:41:11.822
I escaped, Mrs. Wilson.

01:41:11.905 --> 01:41:14.283
I'm free.

01:41:15.701 --> 01:41:18.620
Buddy, I'm so sorry
I wasn't there for you.

01:41:20.330 --> 01:41:23.375
- I should've...
- Now, don't you say another word.

01:41:26.587 --> 01:41:30.299
You was the only one
that was a friend to me.

01:41:31.800 --> 01:41:33.760
And I love you.

01:41:37.264 --> 01:41:40.893
You're the soul
of this town, Mrs. Wilson.

01:41:40.976 --> 01:41:45.105
And you just need to keep doing
what you're doing.

01:42:00.454 --> 01:42:02.372
I washed it.

01:42:17.638 --> 01:42:20.015
Will you come back
into town with me?

01:42:20.098 --> 01:42:22.017
Yeah.

01:42:37.866 --> 01:42:41.203
You know you're
gonna have to go back.

01:42:43.038 --> 01:42:45.624
Yes, ma'am, I know.

01:43:18.574 --> 01:43:20.534
Can I have your keys,
ma'am?

01:43:43.182 --> 01:43:44.266
Well,

01:43:44.475 --> 01:43:47.728
I just talked to Wayne.

01:43:47.769 --> 01:43:50.772
He pretty much admitted
to everything.

01:43:50.856 --> 01:43:55.235
I've known that boy
half my life.

01:43:58.906 --> 01:44:01.825
It just goes to show,
you can know somebody and...

01:44:05.579 --> 01:44:07.498
not know 'em.

01:44:10.125 --> 01:44:13.545
How's his...
How's his head?

01:44:13.629 --> 01:44:15.756
Well, you put
a pretty good dent in it.

01:44:15.798 --> 01:44:18.717
Oh, no, Sheriff,
I told...

01:44:18.801 --> 01:44:20.969
I told the deputy
it wasn't me who did that.

01:44:21.053 --> 01:44:24.097
It was...
It was Buddy Cole. He saved me.

01:44:24.181 --> 01:44:27.226
- No, ma'am. It weren't Buddy.
- Well, yes, it was.

01:44:27.309 --> 01:44:30.813
- Why don't you just ask Wayne?
- I did.

01:44:30.896 --> 01:44:33.232
He don't remember
what happened.

01:44:33.315 --> 01:44:35.567
Head injuries is funny.

01:44:35.651 --> 01:44:40.781
- I'm telling you, it was Buddy Cole.
- What I'm tryin' to say is,

01:44:40.823 --> 01:44:43.158
it couldn't have been Buddy.

01:44:43.242 --> 01:44:45.702
I... I just called up
at the State Hospital.

01:44:45.786 --> 01:44:49.081
- He told me he escaped.
- Ma'am.

01:44:51.041 --> 01:44:53.168
Buddy Cole is dead.

01:44:55.629 --> 01:44:58.132
He hanged himself
in the shower room...

